PayPal Privacy Center
Privacy is built into PayPal.
Your trust is important to us, so we want you to know how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.
Read our privacy statement
Manage your marketing preferences and
learn how you can change your privacy settings
in your PayPal account.
Notice and transparency
We openly communicate about how we collect, process, and share personal information.
Choice and consent
We provide choices to customers about how we use or share personal information.
Security and safety
Your personal information is secure, private, and protected.
Collection
We only collect the data necessary to provide our services.
Sharing and transfer
We share personal information only when legally permitted.
Management
We carefully control access to personal information.
Use, retention, and disposal
We only use and keep personal information for specific business-related purposes.
Access and quality
We maintain accurate records and give customers access to their personal data when requested.
Showing page
Help you pay and get paid
We use your name, email, and shipping address to help you make payments and purchases easily, and we don’t share your full financial information.
Personalize your experience
We use your online shopping activity and purchase history to tell you about products we think you’ll like.
Communicate
with you
We use your data to update you on your PayPal activity and, if you’re subscribed to news and promotions, we’ll send info about other offers and services.
Help protect your account
We use your data to help prevent fraudulent use of your account, meet anti-money laundering requirements, and help keep you and the PayPal community safe.
If you have an account with PayPal
You can change settings and exercise your data rights directly in your account.
